Dear writer,

This message deliberately includes lines that look similar to the boundary.
Here is an example paragraph that is fine:

--BNDRY-LOOKALIKE
Note that the line above starts with two dashes and resembles a boundary,
but it has extra text after BNDRY so a correct parser must not treat it
as the real boundary marker.

Also note: --bndry (lowercase) and - -BNDRY (with space) are not boundaries.

Regards,
